results.title: What Dreams May Come...
results.description: Xavier leaves earth with the mutant Skrulls to become their teacher; The High Evolutionary decides that the best way to solve the mutant problem is to eliminate the mutant gene and turn them all into normal humans; And he does so.

results.title: Heaven's Shadows
results.description: The powerless X-Men launch an assault against the High Evolutionary's satellite to keep Sinister from driving mutations on earth wild; The day is saved and powers return.

results.title: Night of Masques
results.description: The Shockwave Riders attack the X-Men during Carnival and Jean goes down.

results.title: Lost Souls
results.description: The X-Men have their hands full with the Shockwave Riders when a whole new team of bad guys shows up.

results.title: Moscow Knights
results.description: The X-Men are asked to help recover a missing Russian agent and end up running up against a ring of mutant slavers.

results.title: Crimson Pirates
results.description: The X-Men have captured the alien slaver Vogue for the Russian government but his band of super-powered pirates shows up to break him out.

results.title: Shell Game
results.description: The X-Men find themselves split in a battle with the Crimson Pirates but pull together as a team to take down a ring of alien slavers.

results.title: For Those In Peril
results.description: The X-Men rescue Lee's ship from a hurricane.

results.title: Cry Justice, Cry Vengeance
results.description: The last of the D'bari targets Jean Grey in retaliation for his world being destroyed by Dark Phoenix.

results.title: Dream's End Part I: The Past is but Prologue
results.description: Rogue's powers go crazy as she begins to manifest aspects of all of the people she has absorbed over the years; Bishop gets a hard lesson in the Danger Room; Mystique makes her final move to eliminate presidential candidate Robert Kelly and the X-Men race off to stop her.

results.title: Cover #28324
results.description: History of the relationship between Professor X and Moira MacTaggert

results.title: The Good Shepherd
results.description: Following Moira's death, Professor X recalls his history with her and the man who stole her from him; The X-Men try to help Cecilia kick her Rave habit; Storm talks Gambit out of killing Mystique; Wolvie and Rogue delve deep into Destiny's diaries.

results.title: The Legacy Virus Cured--But At What Cost?
The Cure
results.description: Beast finds a cure for the Legacy Virus, but the antidote will kill the first mutant who uses it; While the X-Men play a round of basketball, Colossus uses it; The sad and tragic death of Peter Rasputin.

results.description: Cyclops and Corsair go camping to spend some quality father and son time together.

results.description: Professor X is captured by Magneto; Jean gathers a group of new mutants to help invade Genosha and rescue the Prof (while stopping Magneto).

results.description: Jean Grey's hastily gathered X-Men are dropped into the center of Genosha to confront Magneto.

results.title: Playing God
results.description: A wild new mutant shunts Jean and Wolvie into the nightmare of his mind.

results.title: Poptopia Part One: Useless Beauty
results.description: A new team lineup debuts as the X-Men become involved with an underground mutant colony in London, and Chamber befriends a British pop diva.

results.title: Poptopia Part Two: The Glamorous Life
results.description: The X-Men battle Mr. Clean.  Chamber tries to cope with his fifteen minutes of fame.

results.title: Poptopia Part Three: A Complete Unknown
results.description: Chamber begins to have doubts about his brush with fame and his relationship with Sugar Kane.  Mr. Clean talks with the Church of Humanity.

results.title: Poptopia Part Four: The Clash
results.description: Wolverine kills Mr. Clean.  Chamber is dumped by Sugar Kane and decides to join the X-Men.

results.title: For Unlawful Carnal Knowledge
results.description: The X-Men investigate a mutant brothel, only to be attacked by the Church of Humanity.

results.title: Supreme Confessions
results.description: The X-Men track the Church of Humanity to their base, where Nightcrawler is left unconscious after an encounter with their leader, the Supreme Pontiff.

results.title: Golden
results.description: In a silent issue, Banshee begins assembling the X-Corps.

results.title: Utility of Myth
results.description: The X-Men begin to investigate the X-Corps after they discover that Banshee has been employing criminals.

results.title: Lurking
results.description: The X-Men start to have doubts about the X-Corps and Chamber goes undercover to investigate.

results.title: Army Ants
results.description: Banshee loses control over the former villains in the X-Corps, costing Sunpyre her life.

results.title: Ballroom Blitzkrieg
results.description: Mystique is revealed as the one responsible for organizing the takeover of the X-Corps.  Radius is killed and Banshee has his throat slit.

results.title: Staring Contests are for Suckers
results.description: The X-Men defeat the X-Corps in a battle that nearly destroys Paris.  Abyss sucks Mystique into a pocket dimension.

results.title: Glaubiger, Heiler, Gefallener
results.description: Nightcrawler and Chamber recover from their recent battle with the Church of Humanity.

results.title: Identity Crisis
results.description: Archangel prepares to take down the Vanisher's drug business.  Stacy X aids a dying man.

results.title: Rocktopia Part 8 of 5
results.description: Archangel buys out the Vanisher's drug business, while Nightcrawler learns that the Church of Humanity has plans concerning him.

results.title: Hope Part One
results.description: Professor X invites Sammy the Squidboy to his school after a near suicide attempt.  The Blackbird is shot down, apparently by the Juggernaut.

results.title: Hope Part Two
results.description: The X-Men team with the Juggernaut to battle a mutated Black Tom Cassidy.  Annie and her son Carter are introduced when they discover the catatonic Havok.

results.title: Hope Part Three
results.description: The X-Men defeat Black Tom Cassidy; Juggernaut joins the X-Men, and bonds with Sammy.  Annie is hired as Havok's nurse.  Archangel turns white again.

results.title: Annie's Moving Story
results.description: Annie and Carter arrive at the Xavier Institute.  Husk joins the team and fights with Stacy X.

results.title: Fall Down Go Boom
results.description: Northstar joins the X-Men after he fails to save the life of a young mutant.  Stacy molts.

results.title: Secrets
results.description: Northstar recovers from his injuries, and admits he has a crush on Iceman.  Iceman reveals that his body is turning into Ice.  Angel first displays his healing powers.

items.name: Uncanny X-Men Vol. 2: Dominant Species (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Living in a Mansion
results.description: The Juggernaut destroys the house he grew up in.  Stacy X visits the X-Ranch for a final time.

results.title: Dominant Species Part One
results.description: The X-Men investigate a murder that is apparently linked to a company owned by Archangel

results.title: Dominant Species Part Two
results.description: Archangel, Husk and Wolverine are critically injured in a battle with Maximus Lobo.  Polaris returns to the X-Men and picks a fight with Annie.

items.name: Uncanny X-Men Vol. 2: Dominant Species (Trade Paperback)
Uncanny X-Men Vol. 2: Dominant Species (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Dominant Species Part Three
results.description: Havok wakes up from his coma.  Husk and Archangel have a moment while recovering from the wounds they received last issue.

items.name: Uncanny X-Men Vol. 2: Dominant Species (Trade Paperback)
Uncanny X-Men Vol. 2: Dominant Species (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Dominant Species Part Four
results.description: The X-Men battle Maximus Lobo.  Professor X saves Carter.  Angel realizes that his blood now has a healing factor.

items.name: Uncanny X-Men Vol. 2: Dominant Species (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Rules of Engagement Part One
results.description: Polaris proposes to Havok.  Nightcrawler goes on a leave of absence.  Juggernaut makes up his mind to stay at the X-Mansion.  Alpha Flight comes to remove any Canadian children from Xavier's care.

results.title: Rules of Engagement Part Two
results.description: The X-Men battle Alpha Flight over the welfare of the children in Xavier's care.  Sammy is sent back to his family in Canada.  Polaris murders two members of the Church of Humanity. Stacy X quits.  Nightcrawler finds the first evidence of the Draco.

results.title: Holy War Part One
results.description: The X-Men track down the Church of Humanity after they crucify and murder a number of mutants, including Skin.

results.title: Holy War Part Two
results.description: The X-Men wage their final battle with the Church of Humanity.

results.title: Sacred Vows Part One
results.description: Havok stands Polaris up at the altar.

results.title: Sacred Vows Part Two
results.description: Polaris goes over the edge and tries to kill Havok and Annie.

results.title: The Dead Have No Rights
results.description: Jubilee and Husk fight with a mortician over Skin's funeral arrangements.  Angel uses his new powers to heal a group of children at a local hospital.
